HEADWORD: Ichthyology
<hw>Ich`thy*ol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'ichqy`s</grk>, <grk>-y`os</grk>, a fish + <ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>ichthyologie</ets>.]</ety> <def>The natural history of fishes; that
branch of Zoology which relates to fishes, including their structure,
classification, and habits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ichthyomancy</ent>⟦br⟧
